  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response for vulnerable populations displaced by conflict in Komanda health zone, Irumu Territory in Ituri Province.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the most vulnerable people who largely have settled unsheltered in public places, who are in need of non-food and NFI items. This includes those with special needs (older people, pregnant and lactating women, unaccompanied children, those with disabilities and chronic diseases) who lack shelter and essential items. An unconditional cash intervention is appropriate in the affected area to cover the needs for food (for 15 days), NFIs and hygiene items  for the disabled persons living with chronic diseases. The local market in the area remains accessible and has availability of items. The unconditional cash grants will enable the targeted people to cater to their food stocks  and  purchase essential household items.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, critical protection risks will be addressed, the living conditions of the vulnerable groups will be improved and risk of disease outbreak will be immediately reduced as soon as cash distribution will be done and moderated within 45 days. All non-food-assisted households will be able to cover their non-food item needs according to their habits .  At the end of this project, the beneficiary households will be able to purchase the non-NFIs and other essential items for their households to meet their urgent needs within the 45 days of the project implementation. Above all, the project will have been accountable to the community, through ensuring consultation with representatives and engaging in complaint and feedback mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
